          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-save-model-proposal",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Save Model Proposal",
      "position": {
        "x": 4060,
        "y": 700
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Save Model Proposal",
        "summary": "Treat persistence as a home model, not a file-menu model. `Save` should always write to the current home. `Change Home` should let the user choose where this graph lives now. `Export` should create a copy or fragment artifact. In the `Change Home` dialog, show three layers: current home summary, destination type, and destination details. Destination types should be explicit: Browser Local, GitHub, Hosted Workspace, and later Local Filesystem for the node app. GitHub-specific choices like work/private/public belong inside the GitHub destination details, not at the top of the model.",
        "level": "h3",
        "anchor": "save-model-proposal",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-settings-boundary-findings",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Settings Boundary Findings",
      "position": {
        "x": 3620,
        "y": 700
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Settings Boundary Findings",
        "summary": "The problem is not that graph settings are spread across many tabs. The problem is that they are spread across too many authorities. `DocumentPropertiesDialog` already behaves like the primary graph-settings surface: it owns overview, layout defaults, plugins, theme, GitHub, and now names itself honestly as `Graph Settings & Management`. `PropertiesPanel` should primarily describe the current selection; it no longer offers the full manifest form inline and now hands manifest editing off to graph settings, which is the right direction. The dialog's hidden `system` and `collaboration` tab content has been removed from the live tab model so it no longer carries shadow authorities. `SystemNodesPanel` should remain the graph's reference and health drawer for legend, metadata, scripts, and diagnostics, but not the preferred editing home for deep graph configuration. Target arrangement: graph-level settings live under one graph-settings authority, selection properties stay in the properties panel, and the system drawer remains a graph-native reference surface rather than a competing settings console.",
        "level": "h3",
        "anchor": "settings-boundary-findings",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-task-save-model",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Clarify the file and save model in the toolbar",
      "position": {
        "x": 3180,
        "y": 1060
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "The current file toolbar exposes Save, Change Home, Save Without Expanded, Export Fragment, and boundary-port toggles as a tight row of icons. Clarify which actions are ordinary saving, which actions change the graph's home, and which actions are advanced export operations. Implementation progress: the toolbar now splits home/save from export actions, the destination drawer teaches `current home`, browser-local save is framed honestly as a local copy, and GitHub destination details now use a summary-plus-advanced pattern instead of forcing every repo control open by default.",
        "priority": "critical",
        "status": "in-progress",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "estimateHours": "4",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "The toolbar distinguishes ordinary save from advanced export/re-root operations",
          "A new user can infer which save path is normal",
          "Advanced save/export operations no longer read like undifferentiated icon noise"
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "task",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-task",
