          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "task",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "task"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-properties-vocabulary-proposal",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Properties Vocabulary Proposal",
      "position": {
        "x": 4060,
        "y": 1060
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Properties Vocabulary Proposal",
        "summary": "The properties panel no longer needs a speculative vocabulary sketch; the first real pass has been applied. Nodes now treat semantic `Type` and instance `Name` separately, consumed views are inspect-first, ports are structural instead of buried under advanced authoring, and the generic appearance surface has been reduced to local overrides rather than a style console. Edges now distinguish `Connection` from `Edge`, use `plain.edge` as the baseline relationship type, expose a top-level preview, and treat edge classes as the semantic upgrade path instead of making the UI invent meaning. The remaining work is refinement: cleaner diagnostics wording, stronger type-owned editors, and continued removal of prototype-era controls.",
        "level": "h3",
        "anchor": "properties-vocabulary-proposal",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-task-properties-vocabulary",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Define properties-panel vocabulary and type-sensitive field ownership",
      "position": {
        "x": 4500,
        "y": 1420
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Settle the vocabulary and structural model before polishing the properties panel further. Decide what counts as common structural identity versus type-owned semantic content. Stop leading the UI with implementation terms like `label` when the meaningful field may actually be `Type`, `Name`, `Content`, `Reference`, or `Behavior` depending on node kind. Approved target arrangement: a small common shell, node-type-specific primary fields, `Appearance` as explicit authoring, `Advanced` for raw authoring controls, and `Inspect` for class and bridge diagnostics. Current mapping direction: node sections should organize around `Type`, `Name`, `Content`, `Behavior`, `Appearance`, `Advanced`, and `Inspect`; edge sections should organize around `Connection`, `Meaning`, `Appearance`, `Advanced`, and `Inspect`.",
        "priority": "critical",
        "status": "done",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "estimateHours": "5",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Common structural fields are distinguished from type-owned semantic fields",
          "Properties vocabulary stops conflating implementation labels with product language",
          "A clear `Advanced` versus `Inspect` split exists for the selection surface",
          "Node and edge properties can be reorganized around a semantically honest field taxonomy"
        ],
        "memo": "Completed first implementation pass. Nodes now separate semantic type from view kind, consumed views stop pretending to be editable source nodes, and both node and edge appearance panels have been reduced to override-first surfaces.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "task",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node"
        },
