    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-task-language",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Audit visual language, terminology, and consistency",
      "position": {
        "x": 2370,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Review typography, iconography, labels, component naming, affordance consistency, and graph/browser theme boundaries so the UI reads like one product instead of a collection of individually sensible parts. Current clarification: typography should be treated as a system/document concern rather than a generic appearance panel feature. Primitive text-bearing nodes carry typographic role, while font choice and scale should mostly come from document and structure. Next pass should test that model on markdown nodes, title nodes, and summary/document views before broadening it to the shell.",
