    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-typography-proposal",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Typography System Proposal",
      "position": {
        "x": 2820,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Typography System Proposal",
        "summary": "Typography should be introduced as a bounded text system, not as a generic styling playground. The first usable slice should define text roles such as `title`, `heading`, `body`, and later `caption`/`code`; assign those roles to primitive text-bearing nodes; and let document or summary structure provide font choice, scale, and rhythm. Generic node appearance should stay out of typography except for local color overrides. The first proving surfaces should be markdown nodes, title nodes, and summary/document views before typography spreads into browser chrome or fully custom HTML surfaces.",
        "level": "h3",
        "anchor": "typography-system-proposal",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "root-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "ui-analysis-task-typography-system",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Define a bounded typography system for text-bearing primitives",
      "position": {
        "x": 3420,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Turn typography into a bounded `v1` system instead of a vague design ambition. Open questions to settle: 1. Which text roles exist in `v1` (`title`, `heading`, `body`, and possibly `caption`/`code`)? 2. Which primitive nodes own those roles directly? 3. What comes from document or summary structure versus local node overrides? 4. Which font choices and scale rules belong to the document/system level? 5. How should HTML nodes participate without bypassing the system? 6. Which surfaces prove the model first: markdown nodes, title nodes, and summary/document views, or something broader? Keep the first slice small enough to test in real authored content before attempting shell-wide typography.",
        "priority": "high",
        "status": "in-progress",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "estimateHours": "5",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Typography `v1` defines a bounded set of text roles",
          "Primitive text-bearing nodes are mapped to those roles",
          "Document or summary structure is established as the authority for font choice and scale",
          "The first proving surfaces for typography are chosen explicitly",
          "HTML-node participation is defined without turning typography into arbitrary per-node styling"
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "task",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/task-planning/task.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "root-bridge-task",
