      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Implement theme authority so browser theme remains a browser-level concern, a graph gets its authored theme from a dedicated theme node when present, and individual nodes can still carry local style overrides. The graph should fall back to the browser theme when no theme node exists. Graph settings may expose theme status or a quick handoff, but the theme node itself is the graph's theme authority.",
        "priority": "critical",
        "status": "in-progress",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "estimateHours": "8",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "A graph can declare its theme through a dedicated theme node",
          "Graphs without a theme node inherit the browser theme",
          "Graph settings no longer act as a competing graph-theme editor",
          "Per-node style overrides continue to work over the graph theme"
        ],
        "implementationNotes": [
          "Theme node type scaffolded in the graph editor runtime",
          "Graph theme resolution now prefers a theme node and falls back to browser theme when no node or legacy config exists",
          "Graph Settings now shows theme-node status and create/open handoff instead of editing graph theme directly"
        ],
