      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Define a node authoring contract before reducing properties further",
        "body": "Properties cleanup reached the limit of what vocabulary changes alone could solve. The node authoring contract now exists as a real contract artifact at `/library/documentation/contracts/nodes/node-authoring-contract.node`, using the standard contract nodes plus the TTV shell, and the first contract-driven reduction pass has already been applied to the Properties panel. Current state: node and edge properties are materially cleaner, appearance panels now behave like local override surfaces, and consumed views no longer masquerade as editable source nodes. Remaining work is narrower: type-owned editors, final diagnostics/provenance wording, and continued surface reduction where the shared panel is still pretending to own too much.",
